Package jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.macos

Class Summary
AccountInfoItem This item stores sser account information (username, uid, gid, etc.).
AccountInfoObject The accountinfo object is used by an accountinfo_test to define the object(s) to be evaluated.
AccountInfoState The accountinfo state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified accounts.
AccountInfoTest User account information (username, uid, gid, etc.)
DiskUtilItem The diskutil item holds verification information about an individual disk on a Mac OS system.
DiskUtilObject The diskutil object is used by a diskutil_test to define the disks to be verified on a Mac OS system.
DiskUtilState The package state defines the different verification information associated with a disk on a Mac OS system.
DiskUtilTest The diskutil test is used to verify disks on a Mac OS system.
EntityItemPermissionCompareType The EntityItemPermissionCompareType restricts a string value to more, less, or same which specifies if an actual permission is different than the expected permission (more or less restrictive) or if the permission is the same.
EntityItemPlistTypeType The EntityItemPlistTypeType restricts a string value to the seven values CFString, CFNumber, CFBoolean, CFDate, CFData, CFArray, and CFDictionary that specify the type of the value associated with a property list preference key.
EntityStatePermissionCompareType The EntityStatePermissionCompareType restricts a string value to more, less, or same which specifies if an actual permission is different than the expected permission (more or less restrictive) or if the permission is the same.
EntityStatePlistTypeType The EntityStatePlistTypeType restricts a string value to the seven values CFString, CFNumber, CFBoolean, CFDate, CFData, CFArray, and CFDictionary that specify the datatype of the value associated with a property list preference key.
InetListeningServers510Item An inet listening server item stores the results of checking for network servers currently active on a system.
InetListeningServers510Object The inetlisteningserver510 object is used by an inetlisteningserver510 test to define the object to be evaluated.
InetListeningServers510State The inetlisteningserver510 state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified inet listening server.
InetListeningServers510Test The inetlisteningserver510 test is used to check if an application is listening on the network, either for a new connection or as part of an ongoing connection.
InetListeningServersItem Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the inetlisteningservers510 item.
InetListeningServersObject Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the inetlisteningservers510 object.
InetListeningServersState Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the inetlisteningservers510 state.
InetListeningServersTest Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the inetlisteningservers510 test.
NvramItem This item stores output of 'nvram -p'.
NvramObject The nvram object is used by a nvram test to define the object to be evaluated.
NvramState This state pulls data from the 'nvram -p' output.
NvramTest This test pulls data from the 'nvram -p' output.
Plist510Object The plist510 object is used by a plist_test to define the preference keys to collect and where to look for them.
Plist510State The plist510 state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the specified property list preference key.
Plist510Test The plist510 test is used to check the value(s) associated with property list preference keys.
PlistItem The plist item holds information about an individual property list preference key found on a system.
PlistObject Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the plist510 object and will be removed in a future version of the language.
PlistState Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the plist510 state and will be removed in a future version of the language.
PlistTest Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.10: Replaced by the plist510 test and will be removed in a future version of the language.
PwPolicy59Item The pwpolicy59 item holds the password policy information for a particular user specified by the target_user element.
PwPolicy59Object The pwpolicy59 object is used by a pwpolicy59 test to define the object to be evaluated.
PwPolicy59State The pwpolicy59 state defines the different information that can be used to evaluate the password policy for the target user in the specified directory node.
PwPolicy59Test This test retrieves password policy data from the 'pwpolicy -getpolicy -u target_user [-a username] [-p userpass] [-n directory_node]' output where username, userpass, and directory_node are optional.
PwPolicyItem Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.9: Replaced by the pwpolicy59 item and will be removed in a future version of the language.
PwPolicyObject Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.9: Replaced by the pwpolicy59 object and will be removed in a future version of the language.
PwPolicyState Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.9: Replaced by the pwpolicy59 state and will be removed in a future version of the language.
PwPolicyTest Deprecated. Deprecated as of version 5.9: Replaced by the pwpolicy59 test and will be removed in a future version of the language.
